  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Resting My Horse at Ingyeo Shrine While Traveling to Miryang
  author: Lee Cham
  language: eng
  text: |-
    How many travelers pass this way?
    Few are idle like me.
    Loved mountains make me linger at each turn,
    And I return home alone, reciting verses found.

    Autumn arrives at the mountain temple,
    Dew still clings to the official road.
    At last, I know where to rest this weary frame—
    On the river's bank, where the fishing rocks await.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The poem reflects the poet's contemplative journey, contrasting the bustle of travel with the solace of solitude and nature. Miryang was an important region in medieval Korea, and the shrine (신원) served as a rest station for travelers.
